[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    781[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The demo's ADPKD pipeline uses LOINCs whose canonical units
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    782[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     match the source-system units, so the conversion is a passthrough.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    783[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Production carries a per-LOINC conversion table covering
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    784[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     creatinine (mg/dL <-> umol/L using the molecular-weight factor),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    785[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     glucose (mg/dL <-> mmol/L), hemoglobin (g/dL <-> g/L), and others.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    786[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Quarantine the record rather than guess for unsupported conversions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    787[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    788[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if value is None:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    789[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    790[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if from_unit == to_unit:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    791[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return float(value)
